The Wonders Principle

	Philosophy

		-
			The wonders principle is the notion that any idea, when taken apart from objective
			reality, can be valid, invalid, both, neither, or even something else entirely
			depending on how it is interpreted.
		-

	Principles

		Legitimacy Framework

			-
				A legitimacy framework is a method or set of methods for determining the validity
				of an idea, taken apart from objective reality, in a given context.
